latestIgtvVideos.title: 𝗔 𝗟𝗼𝗼𝗸 𝗕𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗮𝘁 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟬. 📸
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Although this year has been mentally exhausting, my family was there by my side always. They had to be on Instagram because they made my year. Many people were looking forward to 2020 for their business, traveling, weddings, etc. Who knew COVID would enter our Lives?

Honestly, I'm thankful to COVID and Lockdown. This Lockdown allowed me to express myself, to be on the gram, to be happy for the little things we have, to be ready even when no one was watching, to feel good even when things went wrong, to create content, to feel more deeply and to be patient. I've also had personal growth this year. I've made dance videos, styling videos, hair and skincare videos, and whatnot. Futhermore , this year also taught me to be grateful for the things I have, the relationships I have, and not taking anything for granted. 2020 was not that bad after all.

Here are some sweet memories of this year with my family. I hope you enjoy this raw , unfiltered video and relate to it. Also, I'm sorry if this video makes you miss your family and you can't visit them. Not saying this year was the best, but we all had our ups and downs, and we shall get through it.

Bye Bye 2020. Looking Forward to next year. 

What are your thoughts? How was this year ? Do let me know...😊
